message: To maximize your score, always start by combining 'water' with a 'grain' item (rice, wheat, tortilla) to make it soaked. Next, use the 'stove' to cook the soaked grain. Separately, use the 'stove' to cook one 'raw protein' item (e.g., raw beans, raw fish, raw egg) and one 'vegetable' item (e.g., pepper, beet, carrot). message: To get 100 points, always aim for a 3-ingredient dish. First, use water on a grain (rice, wheat, tortilla) to soak it. Then, use the stove to cook the soaked grain, one protein (meat/fish), and one vegetable (if you have multiple, only cook and use one). Finally, combine the cooked protein and cooked vegetable, and then combine that with the cooked soaked grain. This combination of one cooked grain, one cooked protein, and one cooked vegetable consistently yields 100 points.
